-- Meirelles Said to Be Replaced by Rousseff as Head of Brazil Central Bank
-- B y   A n d r e   S o l i a n i   C o s t a
-- 2010-11-23T21:24:45Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-23/meirelles-said-to-be-replaced-by-rousseff-as-head-of-brazil-central-bank.html
Brazilian President-elect Dilma
Rousseff will replace Henrique Meirelles as the head of the
central bank, according to two government officials with direct
knowledge of the matter.  Rousseff will probably pick central bank director Alexandre
Tombini to run the institution, said one of the officials.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Robin Stringer at 
 rstringer@bloomberg.net  